</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub27.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vainne>Vainne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Night-blind Bard</span><br>  Posts: 2232<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(1/14/03 10:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntaverncommonsroom.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4967.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: level</span><hr size=1> Charming takes practice...at least for me it did.<br>
<br>
Something that will help:<br>
<br>
make a hotkey something like the following<br>
<br>
/pet attack<br>
/pet target<br>
<br>
Grab a mob with charm, hit f8 or use your mouse to target the other mob (or assist off the tank if you are in a group), and hit your hotkey.<br>
<br>
Twist some songs. If you want to get fancy with the melee (easier with teh longer duration of charm at level 39) /assist your pet until charm is about to break then hit the hotkey again.<br>
<br>
In other words, charm is Alot easier if you have your pet targeted when it breaks....charming the other mob instead of your original pet will screw up your aggro...<br>
<br>
Don't try and learn to charm with 8 mobs. Learn with 2. At level 30-ish OT by the city is a pretty good place to try, as long as you can make the guards not hate you. Snow cougars in EW are also good, but a little tricker with the adds and (as I remember it) the need for some lev.<br>
<br>
Rockhoppers in Marus or whatever that zone is called would prob be good as well. Maybe pull by Sanctus Seru?<br>
<br>
When your pet gets low on health (easy to see now with the new interface) use fulfils chant to kill it, kiting in a circle. Being able to invis is a nice trick to help with this (there's a ring in Lake of Ill omen with invis to animals I think?)--but not entirely necessary, especially with the shorter duration charm.<br>
<br>
And my final word of advice: don't get too good at kiting...there's alot more fun things to learn being a bard, and some of the best bards I know Never Ever kite.<br>
<br>
Also, if you are good at kiting your defense will never go up.<br>
<br>
Give me a tell in game sometime, if free I'll show you a few things.<br>
<br>
