<br>
Most people in my level range are alts of oobers, and expect me to be able to twist like a 65 Bard or have the kind of oompf that high level Bards they raided uber_mob01 with a few days ago or whatever. Well, I don't. I suck. My gear isn't that great, I can only twist 3 tunes at a time and I don't know how to use a few of my songs every effectively. I hardly make a useful addition to a group.<br>
<br>
Lowering downtime with heal/manasong? Not with KEI for free/cheap these days. Casters tend to be jacked up (I've seen SO many -refuse- to kill without being KEI'd) so the manasong is redundant and they can cast enough heals that my healsong is also obsolete. The group haste I have for melee is only 12% or something, and me taking a chunk of group XP for such a small benifit generally isn't very welcome. At least in my experience as of late.<br>
